content.text:
So basic test works. The issue must be related to `tag_keys` value causing the output to be empty. Looking at the code logic in `influxdb_format`:

Lines 230-243:
```c
if (is_tagged_key(ctx, key, key_len, v->type)) {
    /* Append key/value data into the bulk_head */
    ...
} else {
    /* Append key/value data into the bulk_body */
    ...
}
```

And then lines 257-278:
```c
if (bulk_body->len > 0) {
    /* Append the final bulk */
    ...
} else {
    flb_plg_warn(ctx->ins, "skip send record, "
                 "since no record available "
                 "or all fields are tagged in record");
}
```

The issue is that when ALL fields are tagged (all 3 values are in `tag_keys`), the `bulk_body` is empty, and the record is skipped! This is the intended behavior — InfluxDB requires at least one non-tag field. So my test data needs at least one non-tagged field.

Let me fix the test data to include one non-tagged field:

